GitHub Models is now available in public preview - GitHub Changelog
  URL: https://github.blog/changelog/2024-10-29-github-models-is-now-available-in-public-preview/
  GitHub Models has entered public preview! GitHub Models provides every GitHub developer with access to top AI models via a playground, API, and more.

  --- Content ---
  [Back to changelog](https://github.blog/changelog/)
  
  [GitHub Models](https://github.com/marketplace/models) has entered public preview! GitHub Models provides every GitHub developer with access to top AI models via a playground, API, and more.
  
  ![GitHub Models product screenshot showing the model playground](https://github.blog/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/githubmodels-screenshot.png?w=1024&resize=1024%2C576)
  
  Since the [announcement of GitHub Models almost three months ago](https://github.blog/news-insights/product-news/introducing-github-models/), we’ve shipped a number of enhancements and new models.
  
  New features include:
  
  - **Side-by-side comparisons** – Compare the output of two models as they respond to the same prompt in real time.
  - **Model presets** – Save prompts, parameters, and messages to use later or share with a friend.
  - **Multimodal support** – Provide images in the playground to models that support multimodal capabilities.
  - **Streamlined deployment process** – Quickly move your application from development to production with an Azure production key.
  
  New surfaces to use models include:
  
  - **Models CLI extension** – Use any model from the command line by extending the GitHub CLI with \`gh extension install https://github.com/github/gh-models\`.
  - **Models Copilot extension** – [Install the GitHub Models Copilot Extension](https://github.com/marketplace/models-github) and call GitHub Models with `@models` in GitHub Copilot Chat.
  - **Azure AI Toolkit for VS Code** – Access GitHub Models in VS Code with the pre-release of Azure AI Toolkit, available on the [VS Code Marketplace](https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/items?itemName=ms-windows-ai-studio.windows-ai-studio&ssr=false#overview).
  
  New model ships include:
  
  - **OpenAI o1 models**: Copilot subscribers can use [o1-preview](https://github.com/marketplace/models/azure-openai/o1-preview) and [o1-mini](https://github.com/marketplace/models/azure-openai/o1-mini).
  - **Meta Llama 3.2**: Use the latest multimodal models with [Llama 3.2 11B](https://github.com/marketplace/models/azureml-meta/Llama-3-2-11B-Vision-Instruct) and [Llama 3.2 90B](https://github.com/marketplace/models/azureml-meta/Llama-3-2-90B-Vision-Instruct).
  - **Microsoft Phi 3.5**: Use the new Microsoft Phi 3.5 family of models with [Phi 3.5 MoE instruct](https://github.com/marketplace/models/azureml/Phi-3-5-MoE-instruct), [Phi 3.5 mini instruct](https://github.com/marketplace/models/azureml/Phi-3-5-mini-instruct), and [Phi 3.5 vision instruct](https://github.com/marketplace/models/azureml/Phi-3-5-vision-instruct).
  - **Cohere Command R series 08-2024**: Use the latest Cohere [Command R](https://github.com/marketplace/models/azureml-cohere/Cohere-command-r-08-2024) and [Command R+](https://github.com/marketplace/models/azureml-cohere/Cohere-command-r-plus-08-2024) models.
  - **A21 Jamba 1.5**: Use the latest [Jamba 1.5 large](https://github.com/marketplace/models/azureml-ai21/AI21-Jamba-1-5-Large) and [Jamba 1.5 mini](https://github.com/marketplace/models/azureml-ai21/AI21-Jamba-1-5-Mini) models.
  
  To learn more about GitHub Models, [check out the docs](https://docs.github.com/en/github-models).
  
  **Join our Community**
  
  Join our dedicated [Community Discussions](https://github.com/orgs/community/discussions/142244) to discuss this update, swap tips, and share feedback.
  
